Body: Description: Customer is seeing incorrect data on the open access report. A share will reappear every other scan even after dropping data.

What We've Learned Updated: We are currently troubleshooting other issues with their FS scans for being unable to connect/scan certain systems (Ticket #00418307).

If I recall from when the issue was initially explained to me, a share will appear on the report in Dec, then be missing in Jan, and reappear in Dec.
Next Steps Updated: Clarify issue with customer and if this is a share that is actively being scanned.

Steps to Reproduce Updated: 1. Run Open Access report
2. Verify shares that are not open are there
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Tay Caliguiri, Paul Williams

What We've Learned Updated: **ADCVUTLPACMS100**
- Old report shows entire C & D drive being share
- No shares on this server

**CARVSQLRDSMS003**
- There was a share in January
--- Remediated: 1/28
- Last scan 2/28 - share still shows
- No shares on this server any longer
- Last FSAA Exceptions 1/28 @ 1pm
--- Was skipped in Feb due to being disabled
Next Steps Updated: Now that we have a successful FSAA_Exceptions job for the host in question, Paul will rerun the Open Access report and let us know if the remediated share still shows.
